# List row patterns

Use shared components — do not hand-roll status dots or 3px stripes.

## Registry (master data)

`RegistryListRow` + `RegistryListSkeleton` for catalogs, staff, departments, items.

```vue
<RegistryListRow
  :status-dot-class="activeInactiveStatusDotClass(item.status)"
  :primary-label="item.name"
  :secondary-label="item.code"
  :meta="summaryLine"
  @select="openDetails(item)"
>
  <template #badges>...</template>
  <template #actions><Button>View details</Button></template>
</RegistryListRow>
```

- Status dots → `lib/listRows.ts` (`activeInactiveStatusDotClass`, `catalogTriStateStatusDotClass`, etc.)
- Bulk checkbox → `#leading` slot
- Complex title/meta → `#title` / `#meta` slots with `@select`

## Picker (master-detail sidebar)

`RegistryListRow variant="picker"` + `RegistryPickerSkeleton`.

```vue
<RegistryListRow
  variant="picker"
  :selected="selectedId === row.id"
  @select="selectRow(row)"
>
  <template #actions><AppIcon name="chevron-right" /></template>
</RegistryListRow>
```

## Workflow queue (operational)

`WorkflowQueueRow` + `WorkflowQueueSkeleton` for requisitions, transfers, procurement, walk-in requests.

```vue
<WorkflowQueueRow
  :stripe-class="procurementRequestStripeClass(request.status)"
  interactive
  @activate="openDetails(request)"
>
  <template #actions>...</template>
</WorkflowQueueRow>
```

- Card-style queues → `variant="card"` (walk-in requests)
- Stripe helpers → `lib/listRows.ts`

## Do not migrate

Grid/table layouts (patients, users, roles) — different pattern. Analytics tables stay as HTML tables.
